Suspected Russian drone strikes Turkish tanker in Ukraine’s Odesa, where US natural gas will go. (OBSERVATOR ANTENA 1 via The Associated Press)
Commander of Ukraine’s 225th battalion, Maj. Oleh Shyriaiev, spoke exclusively to Fox News Digital and urged the United States to send Ukraine long-range Tomahawk missiles.

WARNING: GRAPHIC CONTENT - Fox News host Mark Levin questions why there is so much propaganda against the Jewish people and explains why it is so troubling that there is widespread re-writing of history on 'Life, Liberty & Levin.'
A corruption scandal involving President Volodymyr Zelenskyy's associates and golden-toilet luxury threatens Ukraine's leadership amid ongoing war efforts.
Critics says U.S. forces "completely blind" in Niger after losing surveillance bases, hampering rescue efforts for kidnapped American citizen in terror-ridden Sahel region.
New investigation claims Putin uses three identical offices to hide his real location, deceiving the public about where he's actually governing Russia from.
Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy announced major energy sector cleanup Sunday as corruption scandal rocks the nation's nuclear industry.

Rep. Rick Crawford, R-Ark., analyzes the Trump administration’s strategy in Latin America and reacts to reports that the UK has suspended intelligence cooperation with the U.S. on ‘The Big Weekend Show.’
Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy's former business partner accused of masterminding $100 million corruption scheme involving nuclear power company.
The Trump administration stays silent as a $100 million Ukraine corruption scandal rocks Zelenskyy's government, prompting senior official resignations.
New footage reveals North Korean troops clearing mines in Russia's Kursk region, highlighting deepening military ties between Moscow and Pyongyang amid ongoing conflict.

Fox News senior foreign affairs correspondent Greg Palkot reports on politicians and partners of Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy allegedly participating in an energy corruption scandal on ‘Special Report.’
Anti-corruption agencies expose massive alleged kickback scheme at Ukraine's state-owned nuclear power company Energoatom.
Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said the "schemes" in the energy sector are "absolutely unacceptable."
Turkey prepares 2,000 soldiers for potential Gaza peacekeeping mission under U.N. mandate, but Israel firmly rejects Anakara's military presence in the enclave.
Iran claims missile capacity now exceeds pre-war levels after June bombardment of nuclear facilities by Israel and U.S. during 12-Day War conflict.
Fox News correspondent Trey Yingst speaks about the implementations of a broader peace plan regarding the ceasefire and remaining hostages on 'Special Report'.
The Israel Defense Forces said it "eliminated a terrorist who was identified crossing the yellow line and approaching IDF troops in southern Gaza."
Deadly explosions rocked India and Pakistan, killing 20+ people in both countries within 24 hours of each other, as authorities hunt for clues in the attacks.
Trump's America First policy strengthens Israel alliance for strategic deterrence against Iran, experts say. How supporting Israel protects U.S. interests abroad.
Former jihadist commander–turned–Syrian president is set to meet President Donald Trump on Monday, seeking stability, reconstruction aid and the resolution of missing Americans.
Kaveh Madani of the United Nations University warns Iran's severe water crisis threatens regime stability and could impact the country's nuclear ambitions.
Iran smuggled at least $1 billion to terrorist proxy Hezbollah despite heavy sanctions this year, according to U.S. Treasury Department officials.
Syria's Christian population has plummeted from 1.5 million to 300,000. Trump's meeting with Syrian leadership could determine their survival in their ancient homeland.
Many Nigerians welcome Trump’s threat of action over Christian killings, hoping it will pressure their government to protect churches after years of deadly attacks.
Israeli hostage Lior Rudaeff's body was returned Friday following his Oct. 7, 2023, defense of a kibbutz against terrorists who took his body to Gaza.
A plot by "a terrorist network directed by Iran that sought to attack Israel’s ambassador in Mexico" has been thwarted, officials revealed on Friday.

Former Secretary of State Mike Pompeo joins 'America Reports' to discuss President Donald Trump's meeting with Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán to limit purchases of Russian oil with the intention ending the Russia-Ukraine war economically.
North Korea fires ballistic missile days after U.S. War Secretary Pete Hegseth's South Korea visit focused on deterring Pyongyang and strengthening alliance.
Fox News senior correspondent Benjamin Hall presented the first "Honor Award" at the Patriot Awards in Brookville, N.Y., named after his daughter who he credits with saving his life.
